<subSubSection id="C3116565FFEB0844450EFDB7632FFCB5" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB436EEFFEB0844450EFDB7632FFCB5" blockId="4.[264,1323,548,894]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Based on differences in the genital morphology between 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB084447C0FDB76250FDF5" authority="Smith, 1895" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1895" box="[966,1318,548,574]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lubricalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB084447C0FDB76307FDF6" box="[966,1137,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Idia lubricalis</emphasis>
(Smith, 
<number id="3DC324C9FFEB084440D9FDB7626BFDF5" box="[1247,1309,548,574]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="1895.0">1895</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, from the eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F31C767EFFEB084445C9FDDF6572FDAD" box="[463,516,588,614]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">U.S.</collectingCountry>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB08444643FDDF64F4FDAE" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[581,898,588,613]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="lubricalis" subSpecies="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB08444643FDDF64F4FDAE" box="[581,898,588,613]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Idia lubricalis occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from southern California, I elevate the latter to species status as originally proposed by Smith. Superficially, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB0844406FFDE76266FD46" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[1129,1296,628,653]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB0844406FFDE76266FD46" box="[1129,1296,628,653]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">I. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is larger and considerably paler than 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB08444699FD0F6451FD7E" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[671,807,668,693]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lubricalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB08444699FD0F6451FD7E" box="[671,807,668,693]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">I. lubricalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male valve of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB08444015FD0F63D7FD7E" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[1043,1185,668,693]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB08444015FD0F63D7FD7E" box="[1043,1185,668,693]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13302A6BFFEB084440B7FD0F6271FD7D" box="[1201,1287,668,694]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 39" captionStartId="44.[264,362,1525,1549]" captionTargetBox="[378,1208,331,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[378,1213,326,1500]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 39. Male genitalia of the new described species and related species: 22, Idia occidentalis. 23, Idia lubricalis. 24, Drasteria convergens (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 25, Drasteria pulchra (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 26, Drasteria tejonica (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 27, Tarachidia nigra. 28, Oncocnemis duplex (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 29, Oncocnemis helena (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 30, Oncocnemis sala (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 31, Oncocnemis kelsoensis (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 32, Annaphila scurlockorum (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 33, Annaphila abdita (a, valve; everted vesica). 34, Cryphia flavipuncta (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 35, Cryphia albipuncta (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 36, Protoperigea umbricata (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 37, Protoperigea posticata (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 38, Protoperigea subterminata (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 39, Protoperigea parvulata (a, valve; b, everted vesica)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273511/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC324C9FFEB084440EEFD0F6271FD7D" box="[1256,1287,668,694]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
) is straighter than that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB08444619FD5765F9FD16" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[543,655,708,733]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lubricalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB08444619FD5765F9FD16" box="[543,655,708,733]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">lubricalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13302A6BFFEB084446A2FD576588FD15" box="[676,766,708,734]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 39" captionStartId="44.[264,362,1525,1549]" captionTargetBox="[378,1208,331,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[378,1213,326,1500]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 39. Male genitalia of the new described species and related species: 22, Idia occidentalis. 23, Idia lubricalis. 24, Drasteria convergens (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 25, Drasteria pulchra (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 26, Drasteria tejonica (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 27, Tarachidia nigra. 28, Oncocnemis duplex (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 29, Oncocnemis helena (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 30, Oncocnemis sala (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 31, Oncocnemis kelsoensis (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 32, Annaphila scurlockorum (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 33, Annaphila abdita (a, valve; everted vesica). 34, Cryphia flavipuncta (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 35, Cryphia albipuncta (a, valves; b, everted vesica). 36, Protoperigea umbricata (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 37, Protoperigea posticata (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 38, Protoperigea subterminata (a, valve; b, everted vesica). 39, Protoperigea parvulata (a, valve; b, everted vesica)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/273511/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Fig. 
<number id="3DC324C9FFEB084446E6FD576588FD15" box="[736,766,708,734]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) at the point where the valve makes a more pronounced outwards angle. Consistent with its Latin name, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB084447E1FD7F63E7FCCE" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[999,1169,748,773]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB084447E1FD7F63E7FCCE" box="[999,1169,748,773]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">I. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs from California as far north as Wyoming, and east to New 
<collectingCountry id="F31C767EFFEB084447A8FC87637EFCE5" box="[942,1032,788,814]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and Arizona. The 
<typeStatus id="54B0884CFFEB084440FEFC87625DFCE5" box="[1272,1323,788,814]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">type</typeStatus>
locality is Havilah, Kern County, California. 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB0844471DFCAF64B4FC9E" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[795,962,828,853]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lubricalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB0844471DFCAF64B4FC9E" box="[795,962,828,853]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Idia lubricalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F31C767EFFEB084440C2FCAF638EFC9D" box="[1220,1272,828,854]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">U.S.</collectingCountry>
and reaches the Pacific Northwest, where it is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B4D6DFFEB084447AAFCF76324FCB6" authority="Hübner, 1813" authorityName="Hübner" authorityYear="1813" box="[940,1106,868,893]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Idia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B97FEAFCFFEB084447AAFCF76324FCB6" box="[940,1106,868,893]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">I. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
